== Features == [[File:玉手山公園音楽堂.JPG|thumb|right|Antique Music Hall]] * The park encompasses a cluster of ancient Kofuns known as the {{ill|Tamateyama Kofun Group|ja|玉手山古墳群|1=Tamateyama Kofun Group|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamateyama Kofun Group|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamateyama Kofun Group|qq=}}. * At the park's elevated areas lies the "Antique Music Hall," a gazebo built in 1908 during the park’s original establishment. It retains the distinct Western-style architectural elements of the Meiji era, with the logo of the Kawachi Railway Company still affixed at its pinnacle. * During the {{ill|Summer Siege of Osaka|ja|大坂夏の陣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Summer Siege of Osaka|qq=}} in the [[:en:Battle of Dōmyōji|Battle of Domyoji]], Toyotomi retainer [[:en:Gotō Mototsugu|Goto Matabei]] established a fortification on Tamateyama (formerly Komatsuyama), where he died in battle. Monuments and memorials for the fallen of both sides, including a weeping cherry tree dedicated to Matabei, are present within the park. * The park is also associated with the poet [[:en:Kobayashi Issa|Kobayashi Issa]], who visited Tamateyama during his travels in 1795. A stone monument inscribed with one of the haiku he composed there stands within the grounds. * The park houses the {{ill|Kashiwara TV Relay Station|ja|柏原テレビ中継局|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashiwara TV Relay Station|qq=}}, operated by regional television broadcasters.
== Issues and Challenges == {{Unreferenced|date=October 2016|section=1}} * Excessive maintenance costs: In fiscal year 2007, the park's maintenance expenses amounted to 31.38 million yen, comprising 41% of the city's total park maintenance budget. Among this, 21.2 million yen was spent on contracted maintenance services, accounting for 67.4% of the park’s budget. * Restricted nighttime access: The park is locked at night for security reasons, limiting its use for jogging or walking in the early morning or evening. * Lack of clarity in facility usage regulations, such as for the outdoor theater. * Unclear terms in agreements with contractors for managing paid attractions. * Minimal utilization by Kashiwara residents, with most visitors coming from neighboring municipalities. * Deterioration of facilities, such as the outdoor theater and exhibit halls.
Future considerations include evaluating the necessity of attractions, such as arcade games and rides, scaling back operations, and revising lease agreements with the religious corporation.
== Access == * 15-minute walk from [[:en:Dōmyōji Station|Domyoji Station]] ([[:en:Minami Osaka Line|Kintetsu Minami Osaka Line]]) * 20-minute walk from [[:en:Kawachi-Kokubu Station|Kawachi-Kokubu Station]] ([[:en:Osaka Line|Kintetsu Osaka Line]])
